## Frequently Asked Questions

### Do I need a specific charger for Intelligent Octopus Go?

Yes. Intelligent Octopus Go requires a compatible smart charger that can communicate with Octopus Energy's systems. Currently supported chargers include the Ohme Home Pro, Hypervolt Home 3, Myenergi Zappi, Indra Smart Pro, Wallbox Pulsar Plus (via Jedlix), and the Octopus Charge. Standard Octopus Go works with any charger — you just lose the smart scheduling and slightly cheaper rate.

### Is the Octopus Intelligent Go rate really dropping to 3.49p/kWh?

Yes. From 1 April 2026, existing Intelligent Octopus Go customers will see their off-peak rate drop to 3.49p/kWh. This reflects the new Ofgem price cap and government levy reductions. At this rate, a full 60kWh charge costs roughly £2.10 — that's about 1p per mile for a typical EV.

### Can I use Intelligent Octopus Go without a compatible charger?

You can if your **car** is on Octopus's compatible vehicle list — some EVs (notably Teslas and certain BMW/VW models) can be controlled directly by Octopus without needing a compatible charger. However, charger-based integration is generally more reliable and works with any EV. If neither your car nor your charger is compatible, use standard Octopus Go instead.

### Which charger has the best Octopus integration?

The **Ohme Home Pro** has the deepest and most mature Intelligent Octopus Go integration. It was designed in close collaboration with Octopus Energy, and the in-app experience — live cost tracking, charge scheduling, and session history — is the most polished available. The Hypervolt Home 3 is a close second.

### Is it worth upgrading my charger just for Intelligent Octopus Go?

At the new April 2026 rate of 3.49p/kWh (vs 9.5p on standard Go), an IOG-compatible charger saves roughly £126/year for the average UK driver. After the OZEV grant, chargers like the Ohme Home Pro cost around £449 — so you'd break even in under 4 years, less if you drive more than average. Plus you get the convenience of fully automated scheduling.

